column1: # Dataset 4: Bacterial Genome False Positives - Phred Reduction Effect
# Used for: Paired t-test and Cohen's d effect size
# Source: Figure 5 - "reduction of up to eight in Phred scores led to
#         a 70-75% decrease in false positives across both chemistries"
# - These are paired samples (same library sequenced
# - Cohen's d for paired samples uses the mean difference / SD of differences
# - Effect sizes > 2.0 are considered exceptionally large
# - Both chemistries show substantial practical improvement with Phred reduction
